  "post": {
    "id": "post_001",
    "title": "How do you structure nested comments in a React machine coding round?",
    "subreddit": "r/reactjs",
    "author": {
      "id": "usr_01",
      "username": "react_architect",
      "avatarColor": "#ea580c"
    },
    "body": "I have a frontend interview next week and nested comments (Reddit-style) is a common prompt. Curious how you would architect recursive rendering, replies, and expand/collapse without over-engineering.",
    "score": 1247,
    "commentCount": 16,
    "createdAt": "2026-06-21T15:40:19.336Z"
  },
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "cmt_007",
      "parentId": null,
      "postId": "post_001",
      "author": {
        "id": "usr_01",
        "username": "react_architect",
        "avatarColor": "#ea580c"
      },
      "body": "For machine coding rounds, I always start by defining the Comment type and whether the API returns a nested tree or a flat list. Nested is easier to render recursively; flat is easier to mutate.",
      "score": 284,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-22T15:40:19.335Z",
      "replyCount": 6,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "cmt_004",
          "parentId": "cmt_007",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_02",
            "username": "hooks_enjoyer",
            "avatarColor": "#f97316"
          },
          "body": "Flat list + buildTree() is what Reddit actually uses internally. You get O(1) inserts and easier pagination of \"load more replies\".",
          "score": 156,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-22T19:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 3,
          "replies": [
            {
              "id": "cmt_002",
              "parentId": "cmt_004",
              "postId": "post_001",
              "author": {
                "id": "usr_03",
                "username": "redux_purist",
                "avatarColor": "#f43f5e"
              },
              "body": "Do you rebuild the whole tree on every new reply, or patch the subtree?",
              "score": 67,
              "createdAt": "2026-06-22T21:40:19.335Z",
              "replyCount": 1,
              "replies": [
                {
                  "id": "cmt_001",
                  "parentId": "cmt_002",
                  "postId": "post_001",
                  "author": {
                    "id": "usr_05",
                    "username": "senior_dev_42",
                    "avatarColor": "#c2410c"
                  },
                  "body": "Patch the subtree. Keep a Map<id, Comment> for lookups, then attach to parent.replies. O(depth) not O(n).",
                  "score": 41,
                  "createdAt": "2026-06-22T23:40:19.331Z",
                  "replyCount": 0,
                  "replies": []
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "cmt_003",
              "parentId": "cmt_004",
              "postId": "post_001",
              "author": {
                "id": "usr_07",
                "username": "system_design_guru",
                "avatarColor": "#9a3412"
              },
              "body": "Interviewers often give you nested JSON though — so know both approaches.",
              "score": 89,
              "createdAt": "2026-06-22T22:40:19.335Z",
              "replyCount": 0,
              "replies": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cmt_006",
          "parentId": "cmt_007",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_04",
            "username": "tailwind_fan",
            "avatarColor": "#fb7185"
          },
          "body": "Recursive CommentNode is the same pattern as a file tree. Base case: no replies. Recursive case: map replies to CommentNode.",
          "score": 198,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-22T20:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 1,
          "replies": [
            {
              "id": "cmt_005",
              "parentId": "cmt_006",
              "postId": "post_001",
              "author": {
                "id": "usr_08",
                "username": "frontend_lead",
                "avatarColor": "#be123c"
              },
              "body": "Exactly. Split CommentRow (UI) from CommentNode (recursion) — same as TreeRow/TreeNode in a file explorer.",
              "score": 112,
              "createdAt": "2026-06-23T00:40:19.335Z",
              "replyCount": 0,
              "replies": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cmt_011",
      "parentId": null,
      "postId": "post_001",
      "author": {
        "id": "usr_06",
        "username": "junior_on_fire",
        "avatarColor": "#e11d48"
      },
      "body": "Expand/collapse state should NOT live inside the comment data from the server. Keep expandedIds as client UI state keyed by comment id.",
      "score": 173,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-23T03:40:19.335Z",
      "replyCount": 3,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "cmt_008",
          "parentId": "cmt_011",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_01",
            "username": "react_architect",
            "avatarColor": "#ea580c"
          },
          "body": "Yes — otherwise you mutate API payload and can't reset UI without refetch.",
          "score": 94,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-23T05:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 0,
          "replies": []
        },
        {
          "id": "cmt_010",
          "parentId": "cmt_011",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_03",
            "username": "redux_purist",
            "avatarColor": "#f43f5e"
          },
          "body": "Default expand depth 2, then let users collapse threads. Reddit does this with \"collapsed\" author lines.",
          "score": 78,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-23T06:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 1,
          "replies": [
            {
              "id": "cmt_009",
              "parentId": "cmt_010",
              "postId": "post_001",
              "author": {
                "id": "usr_02",
                "username": "hooks_enjoyer",
                "avatarColor": "#f97316"
              },
              "body": "You can also persist collapsed state in localStorage per thread.",
              "score": 45,
              "createdAt": "2026-06-23T08:40:19.335Z",
              "replyCount": 0,
              "replies": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cmt_013",
      "parentId": null,
      "postId": "post_001",
      "author": {
        "id": "usr_05",
        "username": "senior_dev_42",
        "avatarColor": "#c2410c"
      },
      "body": "Don't forget the left border thread line — visual depth matters for UX in nested comments.",
      "score": 121,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-23T11:40:19.335Z",
      "replyCount": 1,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "cmt_012",
          "parentId": "cmt_013",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_04",
            "username": "tailwind_fan",
            "avatarColor": "#fb7185"
          },
          "body": "paddingLeft: depth * 16 plus border-l-2 is the classic pattern.",
          "score": 58,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-23T13:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 0,
          "replies": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cmt_014",
      "parentId": null,
      "postId": "post_001",
      "author": {
        "id": "usr_07",
        "username": "system_design_guru",
        "avatarColor": "#9a3412"
      },
      "body": "For replies, optimistic UI: push to tree immediately, rollback on API failure. Shows you understand async state.",
      "score": 97,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-23T19:40:19.335Z",
      "replyCount": 0,
      "replies": []
    },
    {
      "id": "cmt_016",
      "parentId": null,
      "postId": "post_001",
      "author": {
        "id": "usr_08",
        "username": "frontend_lead",
        "avatarColor": "#be123c"
      },
      "body": "Sorting top-level comments by score vs createdAt is a good follow-up question. Re-sort only roots; keep reply order stable.",
      "score": 64,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-24T03:40:19.335Z",
      "replyCount": 1,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "cmt_015",
          "parentId": "cmt_016",
          "postId": "post_001",
          "author": {
            "id": "usr_06",
            "username": "junior_on_fire",
            "avatarColor": "#e11d48"
          },
          "body": "Stable sort within each sibling group — don't re-sort entire tree recursively on every vote.",
          "score": 38,
          "createdAt": "2026-06-24T05:40:19.335Z",
          "replyCount": 0,
          "replies": []
        }
      ]
    }
